subject: Mapping the Future | From Cloud Next to I/O: What’s new in Google Maps Platform

full_threads.body:
Unveiled at Cloud Next: New Ways to Build with Maps + AI

From powering 10M+ websites to unlocking real-time insights, Google Maps Platform is evolving fast-and Cloud Next delivered big.

Geospatial Analytics in BigQuery
Now you can tap into Google Maps Platform and Earth Engine datasets with no advanced remote sensing or GIS expertise needed.

Weather API in Preview
Display real-time conditions, forecasts, and historical weather.

Build with Generative AI
Combine LLMs with live location data from 20M+ U.S. places to personalize experiences and build intelligent agents.
See What's New

Google I/O Spotlight: Photorealistic 3D Maps Are Here

Announced at Google I/O, Photorealistic 3D Maps are now in Preview for the Maps JavaScript API. With one line of code, devs can build dynamic, cinematic experiences that bring real-world locations to life-complete with rich detail, fluid motion, and spatial depth.
Start Building with 3D Maps

Introducing Places UI Kit: Low-Code. Cost-Effective. Cross-Platform.

The Places UI Kit lets you add data from 250 million places to any map using low-code components. It's a fast, cost-effective way to build consistent, location-rich experiences-across platforms, with less effort, and more real-world context built right in.
Build with Places UI Kit

New Pricing, More Flexibility

Now you can try more Google Maps Platform products for free every month. The updated pricing model gives you the flexibility to explore and experiment with our APIs and SDKs at no upfront cost. It is easier than ever to build and test new ideas for your business.
Learn More

Use the Pollen API to Personalize Experiences

Leverage seasonal data to help users make smarter daily decisions, like avoiding high pollen days.
Explore the API

Celebrate Innovation with Google Maps Awards

To celebrate 20 years of innovation, we're launching the first-ever Google Maps Platform Awards. Whether you're building with AI, transforming retail, or reimagining travel, this is your chance to gain recognition for your work.

Submit your project by July 31st, share your story, and showcase how you're shaping the future of location-based experiences.
Enter your Project

Investing in India

We're making it easier to build in India with Address Descriptors and more platform support.
Watch Investing in India

I/O Connect is Going Global

Google I/O may be over, but the momentum continues!
Join us in Bengaluru.
RSVP Now

Build an AR View of Nearby Places

Enhance your Android app with augmented reality. Learn to display nearby places using Places API and ARCore and anchor virtual objects to your users' maps.
Try the Codelab

Let's keep in touch
